      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The argument that government payments are \"paying people to stay home\" is a common, yet highly charged, simplification. In reality, the structure of modern safety nets is designed to support people through transitions, not to subsidize idleness. Policies that truly discourage work are often those that create excessively high marginal tax rates or benefit cliffs, which are the real structural barriers to employment.",
      "source": "target",
